[{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"EditURL = \"../../../examples/simulate_DCB.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Direct-Column-Breakthrough-simulation","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Direct Column Breakthrough simulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"This example shows how to setup and run a direct column breakthrough simulation as described in Haghpanah et al. 2013 This simulation inolves injection of a two component flue gas (CO2 and N2) into a column of Zeolite 13X initially filled with N2. Adsorption onto Zeolite 13X is modelled with a dual-site Langumuir adsorption isotherm. Injection flow rate is fixed at the rhs of the column and the lhs of the column is open. There is no heat transfer between the column and the column wall","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"First we load the necessary modules","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"import Jutul\nimport JutulDarcy\nimport Mocca","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Then we define parameters which we want. We have defined a structure containing parameters from Haghpanah et al. 2013 which we load now. As we are doing a DCB simulation we will set the heat transfer coefficient between the column and the wall and the wall and the outside to 0.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"constants = Mocca.HaghpanahConstants{Float64}(h_in=0.0,h_out=0.0)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Define-the-model","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Define the model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Next we need to make the model. This model contains information about the domain (grid) over which we will solve the equations and information about the system of equations which we are solving.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Because JutulDarcy has its roots in reservoir simulation we formulate our velocity equation in the following form: q = -frackmufracpartialPpartialx where k is known as the permeability. In this instance we use the pressure drop equation for plug flow in a packed bed:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"v=-frac4150left(fracepsilon1-epsilonright)^2 r_i n^2 frac1mu(nabla P)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"The permeability of the system is then given by:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"k = frac4150left(fracepsilon1-epsilonright)^2 r_i n^2","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"We add the parameters and the desired permeability as an input.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"permeability = Mocca.compute_permeability(constants)\naxial_dispersion = Mocca.calc_dispersion(constants)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"We setup a two component adsorption system. This system type is associated with the appropriate equations and primary and secondary variables.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"system = Mocca.TwoComponentAdsorptionSystem(; permeability = permeability, dispersion = axial_dispersion, p = constants)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Jutul uses finite volume discretisation in space. To model a 1D cylindrical column we setup a cartesian grid with ncells x 1 x 1 dimensions. To ensure we have the correct interface area between cells we set each dimension to the square root of the inner column area.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"ncells = 200\ndx = sqrt(pi*constants.r_in^2)\nmesh = Jutul.CartesianMesh((ncells, 1, 1), (constants.L, dx, dx))","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"The domain also contains the mass diffusion coefficient to calculate mass transport between cells and the thermal conductivity to calculate heat transfer.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"domain = Mocca.mocca_domain(mesh, system)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Create-the-model","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Create the model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Now we can assemble the model which contains the domain and the system of equations.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"model = Jutul.SimulationModel(domain, system, general_ad = true)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Setup-the-initial-state","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Setup the initial state","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"The final thing required to create the simulator is the intial state of the system.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"bar = 1e5\nP_init = 1.0*bar\nT_init = 298.15\nTw_init = constants.T_a","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"To avoid numerical errors we set the initial CO2 concentration to be very small instead of 0.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"yCO2 = ones(ncells)*1e-10\ny_init = hcat(yCO2, 1 .- yCO2)\n\nstate0, prm = Mocca.initialise_state_AdsorptionColumn(P_init, T_init, Tw_init, y_init, model)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Setup-the-timestepping-and-boundary-conditions","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Setup the timestepping and boundary conditions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"For the DCB we are only running the adsorption stage of a VSA process. We will use a total time of 5000 seconds with 1 second timesteps.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"t_ads = 5000\nmaxdt = 1.0\n\n\nnumsteps = Int(floor(t_ads / maxdt))\ntimesteps = fill(maxdt, numsteps)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"We setup boundary conditions for an adsorption stage. AdsorptionBC sets a fixed velocity and concentration and temperature at the inlet and fixed pressure at the outlet. By convention we assume the inlet bc is applied on the left hand side and the outlet bc is applied on the right hand side.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"bc = Mocca.AdsorptionBC(y_feed = constants.y_feed, PH = constants.p_high, v_feed = constants.v_feed,\n                                T_feed = constants.T_feed, cell_left = 1, cell_right = ncells)\n\n\nsim_forces = Jutul.setup_forces(model,bc=bc)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Simulate","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"Now we are ready to run the simulation. For more verbose simulation output info_level can be set to a number higher than 0.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"states, report = Jutul.simulate(\n    state0,\n    model,\n    timesteps,\n    linear_solver = Jutul.LUSolver(),\n    forces=sim_forces,\n    parameters = prm,\n    info_level = 0\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Plot","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Plot","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"We plot primary variables at the outlet through time","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"outlet_cell = ncells\nf_outlet = Mocca.plot_cell(states,model,timesteps,outlet_cell)\ndisplay(f_outlet)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"We plot primary variables along the column at the end of the simulation","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"f_column = Mocca.plot_state(states[end], model)\ndisplay(f_column)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/#Example-on-GitHub","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Example on GitHub","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"If you would like to run this example yourself, it can be downloaded from the Mocca.jl GitHub repository.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_DCB/","page":"Simulate DCB","title":"Simulate DCB","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"CurrentModule = Mocca","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#Installation","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"First install Julia from here. ","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"Mocca can be downloaded by cloning the repository ....","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"git clone mocca ...","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"We recommend running in a specific environment (similar to a virtual environment in python). More information on environments in Julia can be found here.","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"To create an environment in Mocca.jl navigate to the Mocca.jl folder, start the Julia REPL and type the following at the Julia prompt:","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"Pkg.activate(\".\")\nPkg.instantiate()","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"This will activate the environment in the current directory and install all necessary dependencies. Mocca is now installed and ready to use.","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"A good starting example to try is Direct Column Breakthrough simulation. Bear in mind that the first time you run the code in the Julia REPL it may take several minutes to run as Julia needs to compile all the necessary code. As long as you do not close the REPL, the second time you run the code will be much quicker!","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"EditURL = \"../../../examples/simulate_cyclic.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Cyclic-Vacuum-Swing-Adsorption-simulation","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Cyclic Vacuum Swing Adsorption simulation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"This example shows how to setup and run a cyclic vacuum swing adsorption simulation as described in Haghpanah et al. 2013","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"This simulation inolves injection of a two component flue gas (CO2 and N2) into a column of Zeolite 13X. The CO2 is preferentially adsorbed onto the zeolite. Pressure in the column is then reduced to enable desorption of CO2 for collection.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"This is a four stage process comprising:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Pressurisation: where the rhs of the column is closed and flue gas is injected from","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"the lhs, at velocity v_feed, to bring the column pressure up to PH (Pressure High)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Adsorption: Where both ends of the column are open and flue gas is injected from the","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"rhs at velocity v_feed. Pressure at the lhs is PH","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Blowdown: where the lhs of the column is closed and the column is evacuated at","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"PI (Pressure Intermediate)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Evacuation: where the rhs of the column is closed and the column is evacuated from the","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"lhs at PL (Pressure Low).","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Each stage is modelled using the same governing equations but with different boundary conditions.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Adsorption onto Zeolite 13X is modelled with a dual-site Langumuir adsorption isotherm.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"First we load the necessary modules","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"import Jutul\nimport JutulDarcy\n\nimport Mocca","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Then we define parameters which we want. We have defined a structure containing parameters from Haghpanah et al. 2013 which we load now.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"constants = Mocca.HaghpanahConstants()","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Then we need to make the model. This model contains information about the domain (mesh)) which we will solve the equations over and a information about the system of equations which we are solving.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"In this instance we will use the same system as in Haghpanah, which is a two component adsorption system. This system type is associated with the appropriate equations and primary and secondary variables. We also add the parameters and the desired velocity model as an input.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"permeability = Mocca.compute_permeability(constants)\naxial_dispersion = Mocca.calc_dispersion(constants)\n\nsystem = Mocca.TwoComponentAdsorptionSystem(; permeability = permeability, dispersion = axial_dispersion, p = constants)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Jutul uses finite volume discretisation in space. To model a 1D cylindrical column we setup a cartesian grid with ncells x 1 x 1 dimensions. To ensure we have the correct interface area between cells we set dx = sqrt(pi*r_in) where r_{in} is the inner radius of the column.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"ncells = 200\n\ndx = sqrt(pi*constants.r_in^2)\nmesh = Jutul.CartesianMesh((ncells, 1, 1), (constants.L, dx, dx))","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Because JutulDarcy has its roots in reservoir simulation we need to formulate our velocity equation in the following form: q = -frackmufracpartialPpartialx where k is known as the permeability. In this instance we use the pressure drop equation for plug flow in a packed bed. The velocity model specified when instantiating the system automatically calculates the permeability required for input to the domain.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"The domain also contains the mass diffusion coefficient to calculate mass transport between cells and the thermal conductivity to calculate heat transfer","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"domain = Mocca.mocca_domain(mesh, system)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Create-the-model","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Create the model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Now we can assemble the model which contains the domain and the system of equations.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"model = Jutul.SimulationModel(domain, system, general_ad = true)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Setup-the-initial-state","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Setup the initial state","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"The final thing required to create the simulator is the intial state of the system #WRITE #TODO: can this be put in functions","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"barsa = 1e5 #TODO: see if this exists\nP_init = 1.0*barsa\nT_init = 298.15\nTw_init = constants.T_a\n\nyCO2 = ones(ncells)*1e-10\ny_init = hcat(yCO2, 1 .- yCO2)\n\nstate0, prm = Mocca.initialise_state_AdsorptionColumn(P_init, T_init, Tw_init, y_init, model)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Setup-the-timestepping-and-boundary-conditions","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Setup the timestepping and boundary conditions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"Set timesteps","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"t_press = 15\nt_ads = 15\nt_blow = 30\nt_evac= 40\n\nt_stage = [t_press, t_ads, t_blow, t_evac]\n\ncycle_time = sum(t_stage)\nstep_end = cumsum(t_stage)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"cellright = simulator.model.datadomain","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"d_press: Optimize PL [0.05 - 0.5] bar but maybe go even lower (0.01?)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"d_press = Mocca.PressurisationBC(y_feed = constants.y_feed, PH = constants.p_high, PL = constants.p_low,\n                                λ = constants.λ, T_feed = constants.T_feed, cell_left = 1, cell_right = ncells,\n                                cycle_time = cycle_time, previous_step_end = 0)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"dads: Optimize vfeed []","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"d_ads = Mocca.AdsorptionBC(y_feed = constants.y_feed, PH = constants.p_high, v_feed = constants.v_feed,\n                                T_feed = constants.T_feed, cell_left = 1, cell_right = ncells) #TODO: Don't hardcode end cell!","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"dblow: Optimize PI [0.05 - 0.5] bar (should be 0.01 bar diff between dpress and d_blow)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"d_blow = Mocca.BlowdownBC(PH = constants.p_high, PI = constants.p_intermediate,\n                            λ = constants.λ, cell_left = 1, cell_right = ncells,\n                            cycle_time = cycle_time, previous_step_end = step_end[2])\n\n\n                            #TODO: Don't hardcode end cell!","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"devac: Optimize PI [0.05 - 0.5] bar (should be 0.01 bar diff between dpress and d_blow)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"d_evac = Mocca.EvacuationBC(PL = constants.p_low, PI = constants.p_intermediate,\n                            λ = constants.λ, cell_left = 1, cell_right = ncells,\n                            cycle_time = cycle_time, previous_step_end = step_end[3])\n                            #TODO: Don't hardcode end cell!","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"numstages = 4","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"bcs = [d_press, d_ads, d_blow, d_evac]\n\n\n\n\n\n\nnumcycles = 3\n\ntimesteps = []\nsim_forces = []\nmaxdt = 1\n\n\n\nfor j = 1:numcycles\n    for i in eachindex(t_stage)\n        numsteps = t_stage[i] / maxdt\n        append!(timesteps,repeat([maxdt],Int(floor(numsteps))))\n        append!(sim_forces,repeat([Jutul.setup_forces(model,bc=bcs[i])],Int(floor(numsteps))))\n    end\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Simulate","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"#WRITE\nstates, report = Jutul.simulate(\n    state0,\n    model,\n    timesteps,\n    forces=sim_forces,\n    parameters = prm,\n    info_level = 0\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Plot","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Plot","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"#WRITE :\n\noutlet_cell = ncells\nf_outlet = Mocca.plot_cell(states,model,timesteps,outlet_cell)\ndisplay(f_outlet)\n\nf_column = Mocca.plot_state(states[end], model)\ndisplay(f_column)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/#Example-on-GitHub","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Example on GitHub","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"If you would like to run this example yourself, it can be downloaded from the Mocca.jl GitHub repository.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/simulate_cyclic/","page":"Simulate cyclic","title":"Simulate cyclic","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Mocca","category":"page"},{"location":"#Mocca","page":"Home","title":"Mocca","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Mocca Mocca.jl provides a Julia based framework for the simulating pressure / temperature swing adsorption processes for CO2 capture.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Currently there is an implementation of a 4-stage vacuum swing adsorption process for CO2 capture, from a two-component flue gas, using Zeolite 13X and a dual-site Langmuir model. See Direct Column Breakthrough simulation and Cyclic Vacuum Swing Adsorption simulation.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In the future we hope to implement examples of other systems and isotherms e.g. temperature swing adsorption for Direct Air Capture (DAC).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
